<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=101726640618561></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101726640618561><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=101726640618561>My 2cp</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=101726640618561#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=147821><span id=Sage>Aggrok</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>142 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Mar 27th 5:03 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First of all to answer the last post, shamans do not get damage shields but we can make damage shield potions--there are 2 types, one does level/4+1 damage, the other level/2+1 damage, both last level /4 minutes and stack with most all other DS including songs. I understand that with the best potion , best mage DS and bards DS songs that a level 60 character can reach over 130 points in unresistable ( but dispellable ) damage shields. I personally dont use these too often as I always cast Togors Insects on the mob and slow it about 60% ( Im level 47 atm ). The lower leverl DS at level 47 does 13 pts damage and lasts 12 minutes--it trivials at skill level 52 in alchemy. <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   This is the first character I made and I must say that i beleive that shaman class are as close to a true 50/50 mix of casting and magic if played the way I play. I picked Ogres due to highest starting stats overall ( like 31 points more than a human ) and the fact that ogres cannot be stunned from the front--a huge bonus in melee. We are the only class in the game that can haste oursleves and pet, slow the mobs ( best slow spell in the game ), and heal both oursleves and  others. Our buffs our overall the best in the game even though some classes get better buffs in a few area ( clerics Ac, enchanters Haste, etc.) I have gone thru the effort of meleeing my entire life and now have maxed offense and defense and are at 181 2hb skill. Why 2hb? Well because except for the epic there isnt a single shaman usuable spear that has a base damage of over 13 that is easily accessable-most of our piercers have bad ratios ( i do have a spear in range slot for WIs/mana ). I was using a drakkel icegrinder and getting maximum hits of 106 damage not counting the proc until i got a fungus coated tarmok staff recently--30/45 +7 disease damage--i can now hit for 142 max damage at 224 STR ( which will be 255 when i get new buffs at 49 ) and have an attack rating over 900. With alacrity and a pair of SCHW and a hasted/buffed pet, i can solo most blue mobs without even using offensive spells if I choose not to, without nearly as much downtime as if i were to use spells/pet only. My AC hovers around 775 and I have 152 WIS. Too many shamans i see place too much importance on being a &quot; caster only&quot; shaman and go for 200 WIS at all costs. At level 50 200 WIS is only 480 mana more than 152 WIS--thats not an inconsequential number, but if soloing that means u may get off 2-3 more DoTs on a mob before you have to med/cannibalize. Mana regen rate is more important than total mana 90% of the time. Shamans need to melee enought to max out your defense skill so that you get your AC as high as possible--at higher levels casting our Turgurs Insects on a mob ( especially ones that summon ) may get you into melee combat very quickly. All the mana in the world will not help you if you have crappy AC/HP and cant take the damage until the mob is taunted off of you. Being able to melee allows alot more flexibilty for me as I can step in and put in good damage in a small party or take the heat off of my pet while soloing. Granted we will still miss alot even with maxed skills and dont get double attack or what not, but shaman that have invested time to become better in melee will find that from time to time we will actually out aggro a hybrid class like a pally or sk, especially if weilding a weapon that is capable of hits well over 100 damage ever 3 seconds. Our pets are very good, and unless you are just clearing out greenies its well worth it to summon the best pet that you can--he will get in more hits for more damage and get hit alot less. Ive noticed that even the most buffed level 44 pet if it is on the low end cant solo mobs in OT but the highest pet can easily ( all mobs are slowed with Togors ). Early in life our group role will be more healing but as you get close to 50+ you will find that we are woefully inadequate to heal a full party that is pulling mobs at any reasonable rate--you need another healer class or enchanter or both atleast. Its worth it to slow all mobs that are fought, i mem the level 5 slow for low level mobs ( hey , its 20%+ slow for only 20 mana, why not ) and the tougher ones get Togors/Turgurs. I rarely use other debuffs for mobs such as malo-whatever or the incapacitate/listless power spells as they are usually too much mana or the fights are too short. <br>     Well I hope this post will encourage a few fellow shaman to take up arms and get into the fight once in a while ( and no i dont melee in a full group-I slow/heal/buff like a good shaman :) ). Practice all 3 of your weapon skills, but past level 20-25 you will not be using 1hb all that much. 2hb weapons are typically cheap as melee and hybrid classes will almost alwasy be using 2hs or dual weilding do to better damage/delay. Because of the long delay of 2hb and the damage caps they arent worth using really until level 20+. But pick yourself up a nice 2hb at EC or wherever when you can and start practicing--Drakkel Icegrinders are 27/45 and proc a 30dd ice spell at level 1 and can be had for as little as 200pp on Luclin server now. Yeah they suck stamina but we have spells to replensih / buff that so dont worry. Please dont wait until level 40 and realize you only have 80 defense and cant hit a mob for more than 20 damage cause you always sat in the back of the group and cast spells thru your life--it get very hard at later levels to raise skills in melee cause even light blues can double 50 hit you--not fun. <br>  Well enuff said here, go out and enjoy the game!<br><br>47 Ogre Shaman on Luclin Server--Aggrok<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
